---
description: Never add Cursor co-author trailers to git commits
alwaysApply: true
---

When creating git commits in this repository:

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent@cursor.com`, or any AI/Cursor co-author trailer.
- Do **not** append co-author lines to `git commit -m` messages or HEREDOC bodies.
- Commits must list only the human author unless the user explicitly names a different human co-author.

The repo strips and blocks these trailers via Husky hooks; including them causes failed commits or blocked pushes.
